//assumption - npm, grunt are installed in system
1. set application's root path to app folder in console(for running front-end server using grunt)

2. Run grunt serve / sudo grunt serve in console (path pointing to app folder)

3. Start ruby server at localhost:3000

4. goto http://localhost:9000/


#for a fresh project
Run npm install (dependencies are currently there in node_modules, so application will run without npm install)

Run grunt for compiling any live change in scss file to css (final css is currently there, so  style.css will work without grunt )